    "The second line of Eq.",
    "(5) is the strain amplitude produced by each individual eccentric SMBHB binary, cast as the sum of harmonics fulfilling the condition f K,r = f (1 + z)/n.",
    "In that expression, h(f K,r) is the strain of the equivalent circular binary emitted at twice the orbital frequency of the system, as given in Eqs.",
    "(4)-(7) of Rosado et al. (2015), and g(n, e) is a combination of Bessel functions (see, e.g.",
    "Bonetti & Sesana 2020, for details)."
